==Into the Factory==
* '''Player:''' Hello Carol.
* '''Carol:''' What puny human worker want?
* '''Player:''' You've been treating your staff terribly and I'm here to put a stop to it!
* '''Carol:''' Puny human worker make me laugh. Me has targets to meet, workers must meet targets.
* '''Player:''' No. They're overworked and underpaid and this will stop now!
* '''Carol:''' If puny human worker want to help puny human will go work with them.
* '''Player:''' No, you will stop this slavery now!
* '''Carol:''' Puny human worker will leave now.
* '''Player:''' I'd better go and speak to Holly.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Carol again===
* {{tmissing}}

===Back to Holly===
* '''Player:''' I tried speaking to Carol but she just won't budge. Do you have any ideas?
* '''Holly:''' Perhaps we should try and ignite Carol's Christmas spirit... help her to see that work and targets isn't what Christmas is about.
* '''Player:''' That might work, how do you propose we do that? Do Trolls even care about Christmas?
* '''Holly:''' Carol once spoke about her favourite gift from a previous Christmas, if you could find that and give it to her it should remind her that Christmas is a time of joy.
* '''Player:''' Good idea, where should I start looking?
* '''Holly:''' We have storage chests in the factory, you should start there.
* '''Player:''' Okay, thanks.
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the storage chest===
* {{tbox|pic=Battered teddy detail.png|You rummage around in Carol's chest and find an old battered teddy bear among paperwork and other trollish items.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using teddy on Carol===
* '''Player:''' I've found your teddy... Doesn't this remind of what Christmas is about?{{Sic}}
* {{tbox|pic=Battered teddy detail.png|You hand the teddy to Carol.}}
* '''Carol:''' Carol remembers... but that was past. I am business troll now and targets must still be met.
* '''Player:''' But think of the people... don't they deserve to feel good about Christmas?
* '''Carol:''' Targets must be met!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Holly once more===
* '''Player:''' I gave Carol her old gift but she says that was the past and she is focussed{{sic}} on business now.
* '''Holly:''' We'll have to try something else, perhaps a new gift could make her feel differently.
* '''Player:''' Where could we get a Christmas gift?
* '''Holly:''' We're making them in factory!{{Sic}} You'll have to find out what kind of gift would be suitable though!
* '''Player:''' How can I do that? I don't think Carol will just tell me what she wants.
* '''Holly:''' The other staff probably know her best, you'll have to ask them for the information.
* '''Player:''' Okay I'll try that, thanks.
* {{tact|end}}

