===Using the present on Carol===
* '''Player:''' I have a present for you!
* {{tbox|pic=Red paper hat detail.png|You hand Carol your freshly crafted Red paper hat.}}
* '''Carol:''' This good, Carol likes this!
* '''Player:''' Doesn't it feel good to receive gifts? Now will you cut your workers some slack?
* '''Carol:''' Haha puny human is funny. Get back to work.
* {{tact|end}}

===Back to Holly again===
* '''Player:''' I made a{{sic}} Carol a new present and she liked it but it still hasn't convinced her.
* '''Holly:''' Blasted Trolls... What do you think we should do?
* '''Player:''' Well, reminding Carol of the past and improving her present didn't work... we need to convince her the future will be better if she changes her ways.
* '''Holly:''' Carol is business minded so she should always be looking ahead, this might work!
* '''Player:''' The only problem is we have no way of seeing the future...
* '''Holly:''' Indeed we can't see the future [player], but I know someone who can... the Oracle!
* '''Player:''' Where can I find this Oracle?
* '''Holly:''' The Oracle resides atop Ice Mountain, between Edgeville and Falador.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Okay I will go and speak to the Oracle.}}
** '''Player:''' Okay I will go and speak to the Oracle.
** '''Oracle:''' Hello? Is this thing working?
** '''Player:''' What? Who? I'm hearing voices!
** '''Holly:''' That will be the Oracle I'm guessing.
** '''Player:''' Oracle, I seek your wisdom to save Christmas.
** '''Oracle:''' Do not speak [player]. I foresaw your request and I have what you seek.
** {{qact|The screen fades to black and transitions to beneath the factory, inside the Chambers of Xeric.}}
** '''Worker:''' So tired... must find somewhere better to sleep than those lice ridden blankets.
** {{qact|Ulina walks into a big room, when suddenly the Great Olm appears.}}
** '''Worker:''' {{overhead|What...}}
** {{qact|The screen cuts to an animation of a kitten playing with a ball.}}
** {{tbox|We interrupt this harrowing scene with a soothing picture of a kitten. Please do not think about what happened to Ulina - she found peace.}}
** {{qact|The screen fades back to Holly and the player.}}
** '''Player:''' Thank you Oracle!
** '''Player:''' Holly! The Oracle showed me what's going to happen! Ulina is going to die!
** '''Holly:''' Oh no! You must tell Carol, even she won't want this!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|That's too far, go yourself.}}
** {{tmissing}}

==Telling Carol about the future==
* '''Player:''' Carol, I've seen the future! If you don't change your ways Ulina is going to die!
* '''Carol:''' Hahaha, nice try human... get back to work!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Holly===
* '''Player:''' Carol won't believe me that Ulina is going to die! What should we do?
* '''Holly:''' I guess it is a little farfetched, especially coming from a human... Maybe you can turn yourself a ghost or something?
* '''Player:''' I did see some beds in the factory, I could use one of the sheets!
* '''Holly:''' Good idea but you must hurry [player], we don't know how long Ulina has left!

===Searching the beds===
* {{tselect|Take and wear the sheet?}}
* {{topt|Yes}}
** {{tbox|You throw the sheet over yourself and start to itch. But at least you look slightly ghostly, if a little grubby.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No}}
** {{tmissing}}

===Haunting Carol===
* '''Carol:''' Eeeeek! A ghost! Please don't hurt Carol.
* '''Player:''' Carol... I am the ghost of Christmas future... you must change your ways...
* '''Carol:''' But Carol doing good, targets are being met.
* '''Player:''' You must take care of your workers Carol. Money isn't everything.
* '''Carol:''' Money is everything to business troll. What happens if Carol not change?
* '''Player:''' Your workers are so tired they will wander deeper in to the cave to search for somewhere to sleep.
* '''Player:''' Ulina will wander too far and she will not return. How will your targets be met if your workers die Carol?
* '''Carol:''' Carol not want Ulina to die. That human worker was right. Carol is bad boss and Carol is sorry.
* '''Player:''' It is not too late Carol, you can still change things for the better.
* '''Carol:''' Carol is bad boss. Carol has failed to meet targets. Carol will return to Wiss{{sic}} now...
* '''Player:''' No Carol, you must stay and make the presents for Christmas!
* {{qact|Carol disappears as the screen fades to black.}}
* {{tbox|Carol hurriedly leaves the factory and runs away.}}
* '''Player:''' I'd better go and tell Holly the good news.
* {{tact|end}}

===Telling Holly the news===
* '''Player:''' It worked! Carol has gone! You're all free!!
* '''Holly:''' Gone? What!? We were always free, we just wanted better working conditions! You idiot... how are we going to make the presents now!?
* '''Player:''' But I thought you hated Carol? Can't you work without a boss?
* '''Holly:''' We can make presents but now we have no one to manage deliveries and shipping... you've ruined Christmas!
* '''Player:''' Wait! What about Diango? He's always making presents and might be able to help you out?
* '''Holly:''' You had better hope so [player]. Go and speak to Diango and let me know as soon as possible!
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can I get a teleport back to Port Sarim?}}
** {{qact|The player is teleported back outside Port Sarim.}}
* {{topt|Ok, I'll go find Diango.}}
** {{tmissing}}

==Asking Diango for help==
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Ask about Christmas workers.}}
** '''Player:''' Can you help me? We need to save Christmas!
** '''Diango:''' That depends... what do you need? A dragon kite?
** '''Player:''' Not exactly. I kind of need you to hire a team of workers from another Christmas Factory.
** '''Diango:''' WHAT? Why?
** '''Player:''' I ruined Christmas by putting a stop to their slave labour camp, apparently.
** '''Diango:''' Well... I... In that case well done, I think. And it just so happens I can help, I'm short of staff right now so I'll hire everyone I can get.
** '''Player:''' That's great! I'll go and tell Holly the good news!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Spinning plates?|event=no}}
* {{topt|I'd like to check holiday items please!|event=no}}
* {{topt|What else are you selling?|event=no}}
